  "texts": [
    "With traditional transactions, the jurisdiction is typically determined by the physical location of the parties involved or the location where the transaction occurred.",
    "However, with blockchain-based transactions, the parties involved may be located in different countries, and the transaction may occur entirely online.",
    "The lack of a physical location makes it difficult to determine which legal system applies to the transaction.",
    "This can create legal uncertainty, as different legal systems may have different laws and regulations that apply to the transaction.",
    "In addition, the lack of a central authority to oversee blockchain transactions makes it difficult to enforce legal decisions across borders."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}